    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add the <strong>remaining sliced garlic</strong> and your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>thyme</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potato</strong> with the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 15-18 min or until the potato is fork-tender</p>",
